{{Orphan|date=July 2015}}
{{Infobox company | name = Dangerous Mathematicians | logo = | type = [[Private company|Private]] | genre = | foundation = 2005 | founder = Karen Patwa | location_city = [[Brooklyn]], [[New York (state)|New York]] | location_country = [[United States]] | key_people = | industry = [[Clothing design]] | products = Women’s tailored suits, women’s wedding suits, women’s formal suits | services = | market cap = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | assets = | equity = | owner = | num_employees = | parent = | divisions = | subsid = | homepage = {{url|DangerousMathematicians.com}} | footnotes = | intl = }}
'''Dangerous Mathematicians''' is an American fashion business founded by Karen Patwa in 2005 and based in Brooklyn, New York. The company designs and sells lesbian wedding suits which blend the masculine elements of a tuxedo with the feminine qualities of a dress.<ref>http://www.weddingprideny.com/stories/2013/3/wp_suits_2013_bk_2013_3.html</ref>
Dangerous Mathematicians’ name is based on Patwa’s career as a math and physics instructor.<ref>http://thebrooklynink.com/2010/03/23/9392-the-most-dangerous-designer-in-brooklyn/</ref> Geometric principles from math and science serve as sources of inspiration for Dangerous Mathematicians designs.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://50.56.218.160/archive/category.php?category_id=27&id=33744|title=Designer Brings Math-Inspired Clothing Home to Brooklyn|website=50.56.218.160}}</ref> [[File:Lesbian wedding in New York.jpg|thumb|Lesbian wedding in New York with dresses made by Dangerous Mathematicians|right]]
==History== Dangerous Mathematicians first opened its store in 2006 on the Lower East Side of Manhattan. The company originally offered ready made and bespoke professional attire options for “smart women.” <ref>http://authenticorganizations.com/harquail/2010/04/06/capturing-authenticity-in-your-business-name-dangerous-mathematicians/</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://nymag.com/news/articles/reasonstoloveny/2008/52925/index5.html|title=24. Because Our Schoolteachers Are Such Prim Homebodies|website=NYMag.com}}</ref> The original Rivington Street location frequently hosted themed parties for its clientele featuring photoshoots, fashion shows and math contests.<ref>http://www.brynmawr.edu/alumnae/bulletin/nov10/cf.html</ref> Patwa designed her first women’s wedding suit in 2007.
In 2010, the company relocated to Boerum Hill, Brooklyn, in an area where there are many small boutiques.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.wsj.com/news/articles/SB10001424052748704852004575258583234726118 | work=The Wall Street Journal | first=Sushil | last=Cheema | title=Boerum Hill Packs Variety in a Leafy Pocket | date=2010-05-22}}</ref>
In response to an increase in demand for wedding suits after [[Same-sex marriage in New York|the legalization of gay marriage in New York]] in June 2012, Dangerous Mathematicians' head designer Patwa created a line exclusively geared towards lesbians.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/new-york/happy-anniversary-article-1.1119445 |title=Happy anniversary! |publisher=NY Daily News |date= 2012-07-22|accessdate=2013-10-30 |location=New York}}</ref> As of 2013, Dangerous Mathematicians has evolved to focus exclusively on bespoke women’s suits.<ref>{{cite news|last=Campbell |first=Andy |url=http://www.nypost.com/p/news/local/brooklyn/boerum_hill_has_new_place_to_get_GG4oqYVnM1lVcqxUYafGBK |title=Boerum Hill has a new place to get suited up &#124; New York Post |publisher=Nypost.com |date=2010-03-10 |accessdate=2013-10-30}}</ref>
==Reception and Competitors==
Dangerous Mathematicians has been featured in a variety of gay-oriented publications such as Wedding Pride, Rainbow Wedding Network, and Huff Post Gay Voices. More recently, other women’s suit businesses have introduced themselves to the market, such as Fourteen, Tomboy Tailors, and St. Harridan.
